Japanese computer-game giant Nintendo Co. Ltd. said  Monday its pre-tax earnings plunged 44 percent from a year earlier to 92.8  billion yen (900 million dollars) in the year to March.
Sales dived 23.5 percent to 486 billion yen in the same period.
Nintendo forecast an improved profit of 110 billion yen for the current  year although sales were projected to decline to 450 billion yen.
